[2] Mumps: USA (Massachusetts)
Date: Wed 13 Apr 2016
From: A trusted source who prefers to remain anonymous

As of 29 Mar 2016, there have been 19 confirmed and 30 suspect cases of mumps at Harvard University [Massachusetts]. A letter was sent to prospective students from the Office of Admissions and Financial Aid recommending that those who have not been vaccinated, not visit the campus due to their increased risk of contracting the virus. Likewise, those who may have been exposed to mumps or know they are infected with it, not visit campus for the health and safety of others. Harvard University Health Services has been working closely with the Massachusetts Department of Public Health and the Cambridge Public Health Department to track and monitor the situation. Procedures are in place to protect current students and visitors.



[In 2006, the United States experienced a multi-state mumps outbreak involving more than 6500 reported cases. This resurgence predominantly affected college-aged students living in the Midwest, with outbreaks occurring on many different Midwestern college campuses.

In 2009 to 2010, 2 large outbreaks occurred. One multi-year outbreak involved about 3000 people and mostly affected high school-aged students who were part of a close-knit religious community in New York City and attended schools in which they had very close contact. The outbreak started when an infected student in this religious community returned from the United Kingdom where a large mumps outbreak was occurring.

The 2nd outbreak involved about 500 people, mostly school-aged children, in the U.S. Territory of Guam.

In 2011-2013, there were several smaller mumps outbreaks reported on college campuses in California, Virginia, and Maryland. However, these all had limited spread, and national case counts for these years were at usual levels (several hundred cases per year).

Excerpted from http://www.cdc.gov/mumps/outbreaks.html.

Mumps activity seems to be high this year (2016), but the case numbers to date are lower than 2014 and 2015, i.e., 1223 and 1057, respectively. While it is only April, spring semester in colleges will be ending soon.

A map showing Massachusetts can be accessed at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=4162668,4323. - Mod.LK

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=4162668,4323.]
